        <section class="subject-introduction">
            <div class="container">
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-12">
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-lg-8 col-12">
                        <h1>Why study Engineering at Queen&#x27;s University Belfast?</h1>
<p>From Chemical to Aerospace and Mechanical to Product Design, Engineering at Queen's spans a huge range of specialisms – so however you plan to change the world, a Queen's degree will help you. You'll study at one of Queens' unique Engineering Schools, each of which contributes towards leading advances in science and technology with a real-world impact.</p>
<ul>
<li>World-class Engineering facilities including state-of-the-art laboratories, high-load capacity strength analysis equipment and automotive test cells.</li>
<li>An impressive collection of alumni, including Maire O'Neill – winner of British Female Inventor of the Year 2007 and the 2014 Royal Academy of Engineering Silver Medal.</li>
<li>Paid industry placements and work experience opportunities depending on your degree.</li>
<li>Internationally-excellent research facilities such as the Northern Ireland Technology Centre, the Sustainable Energy Research Centre and the Queen's Advanced MicroEngineering Centre.</li>
</ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-lg-4 col-12">
                        
<div class="promotion-banner image-only">
    <img class="mw-100" alt="Top 125 in the world for Engineering and Technology (Times Higher Education World University Rankings 2020)" src="https://ctfimages.intoglobal.com/xw2h6mjophtz/P7NV5BZHZoEvCIxKntBFj/9d1c458ddd44346ae95d959407a5157f/QUB_Engineering_USP.svg?fit=fill&w=300&h=300&q=80" />
</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
